Next, let's explore some basic statistical functions. np.sqrt() : square root of a number np.abs() : absolute value of a number np.power() : the power of a number np.log() : muliplying arrays np.exp() : dot product of two arrays np.min() : minimum value of a set of numbers np.max() : maximum value of a set of numbers Note: numpy has a lot of mathematical functions available to use, for more visit NumPy . In [15]: Copied! # Statistical functions sqrt = np . sqrt ( 81 ) abs = np . abs ( - 9 ) power = np . power ( 2 , 10 ) log = np . log ( 9 ) exp = np . exp ([ 9 ]) min = np . min ( a ) max = np . max ( b ) # Display results print ( f " sqrt: { sqrt } 
